article.description: — Jake Stephens had 26 points in Chattanooga's 82-71 win over Gardner-Webb on Saturday.
article.headline: Stephens scores 26, Chattanooga beats Gardner-Webb 82-71
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- — Jake Stephens had 26 points in Chattanooga's 82-71 win over Gardner-Webb on Saturday. Stephens added nine rebounds and five blocks for the Mocs (5-3). Dalvin White scored 12 points and added five assists and Jamaal Walker had 10 points. The Runnin' Bulldogs (2-6) were led in scoring by Julien Soumaoro, who finished with 14 points and five steals. Anthony Selden had 11 points, seven rebounds and two blocks. Gardner-Webb also got 14 points from DQ Nicholas. It was Gardner-Webb's first home game this season. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
